text: Michael Schaeffer House is a historic home located at Evansville, Indiana. It was built in 1894, and is a two-story, Queen Anne style red brick dwelling. It has a slate roof and limestone detailing. It features an Eastlake Movement style entry porch. Note: This includes and Accompanying photographs It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1982. ==References== Evansville Category:Queen Anne architecture in Indiana Category:Houses completed in 1894 Category:Houses in Evansville, Indiana Category:National Register of Historic Places in Evansville, Indiana
